para_trans: On deputation to the post of Deputy Tehsildar
Partial change in the given position
Government Decision No: Representation-2024 / Q. No.202 / E-9
Madam Cama Marg, Martyr Rajguru Chowk,
1) Revenue and Forest Department Government Order No. Transfer-2024 / Q. No. 176 / E-9, D. 13.09.2024

Subject to the terms and conditions prescribed in Annexure-II to the Maharashtra Civil Services (Period of Incorporation, Subordinate Service and Provisions during Suspension, Dismissal and Removal from Service) Rules, 1981, Rule-40, Mr. Vinod Kumar Sadashiv Chavan, Resident Deputy Tahsildar, Tehsil Office Dindori, G. Nashik has been appointed as "Deputy Tahsildar (Revenue), Tehsil Office Sangli, G. Sangli" by order hereunder. However, read on for administrative reasons: Mr. Chavan's position in the order here has been partially changed to his revised position in the following table in Column No. The position mentioned in 4 is being done.
(2) The officer concerned shall immediately assume the office of the post granted by partial transfer under this order.
The decision is available on the Government of Maharashtra's www.maharashtra.gov.in website.
table_trans: Naib Tehsildar (Revenue), Tehsil Office Sangli, District Sangli
Naib Tehsildar (Unauthorized Non-Agriculture Branch), Collectorate Sangli, District Sangli
